                            <p class="text-left leading-relaxed text-gray-800 text-sm mb-5 pl-0 md:pl-5"><strong>DLSU-D 95.9 Green FM, also known as Green FM or La Salle Radio, is the official campus radio station of De La Salle University–Dasmariñas,</strong> operating on 95.9 MHz FM with a 10-20 watt transmitter reaching a three-kilometer radius.</p>
                            <p class="text-left leading-relaxed text-gray-800 text-sm mb-5 pl-0 md:pl-5">Established in August 2005 with the call letters DWSU assigned by the NTC, the station began under the Communication Arts Department (now Communication and Journalism Department) led by Chair Ms. Rosanni Recreo Sarile.</p>
                            <p class="text-left leading-relaxed text-gray-800 text-sm mb-5 pl-0 md:pl-5">Initially supervised by Professor Maria Aurora Quadra-Balibay from 2007 to 2019, the role of station manager was passed to Mr. Artin Umali, who continues in this role today.</p>
